<TITLE> Fakhruddin congratulates new Nepali PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 16 (bdnews24.com/reuters)  Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Saturday felicitated Pushpa Kamal Dahal on his election as prime minister of Nepal, the foreign ministry said in a press statement. Fakhruddin said he was confident that under his astute and dynamic leadership Nepal would attain greater height of peace and prosperity. He also wished the new prime minister long life, health and happiness. Nepali lawmakers elected Dahal, a Maoist who led an insurgency against the monarchy as the country's new prime minister on Friday. Dahal won 464 of the 577 votes cast in a special Constituent Assembly voting to defeat Sher Bahadur Deuba, a three-time former prime minister. bdnew
